    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your concern, but even a single dose of ibuprofen can be dangerous for someone on warfarin. The risk of bleeding isn't just about taking multiple doses; it's about the interaction between the two medications. Warfarin affects how your blood clots, and ibuprofen can inhibit the clotting process, leading to an increased risk of bleeding, even with just one pill. This can be serious and potentially life-threatening. It's always best to consult with your healthcare provider for safe alternatives. I can't stress enough how important it is to follow their guidance. Your neighbor's experience doesn't guarantee the same outcome for you due to individual differences in health and medication interactions. Let's find a safe solution together.",
